<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-27T15:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-27T15:45:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72112/1399½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Windsor, Vt.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27T15:45:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915—3:45 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Instructions of Sir Edward Grey to Ambassador about cotton gives me deep
                                concern.<note n="82" xml:id="d259fn1">See telegram No. 2510, July
                                22, 1915, from the Ambassador in Great Britain, <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_193">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                                    193</ref>.</note> Am I mistaken in my recollection that the
                            British Government formally notified us that cotton would be regarded as
                            not already contraband and would be continued to be so treated?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>